ZCZC EE72
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
SUNDAY TO WEDNESDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND MARITIME AGENCY
AT 222300 UTC
THIS PERIOD SHOULD BE CHARACTERISED BY A PAIR OF MAJOR LOWS IN TURN COMING
TO OCCUPY SIMILAR POSITIONS IN THE N ATLANTIC KEEPING A WEAK RIDGE OF HIGH
PRESSURE LARGELY OVER CONTINENTAL EUROPE THROUGHOUT. THE FIRST MAIN LOW IS
EXP OFF SERN ICELAND WITH CENTRAL PRESSURE NEAR 980 TO START THE PERIOD.
THIS LOW SHOULD FILL AND MOV AWAY NE INTO THE NEW WORKING WEEK AS ANOTHER
MAJOR AND COMPLEX LOW MOVS INTO THE N ATLANTIC IN ITS WAKE PERHAPS DEVELOPING
TWIN CENTRES IN THE AMBIT OF ICELAND BY THE END OF THE PERIOD. NO HAZARDOUS
WINDS ARE EXP ACROSS NITON TO END THE WEEKEND AND BEGIN THE FLW WORKING WEEK.
THIS WILL LIKELY GIVE WAY TO A SWATHE OF SEV GALES ARRIVING IN SHANNON EARLY
TUESDAY PERHAPS BRIEFLY STORM HERE BEFORE SPREADING BODILY EWARDS THROUGH
NERN NITON TO MIDWEEK BUT PROBABLY NOT REACHING ENGLISH CHANNEL NITON AREAS
IN THE PERIOD
